text: So I casually play a game on my phone that is all about in app purchases(Final Fantasy Record Keeper) and the developer just announced a new player targeted event to let newer players "catch up" to the established people. All the long time players are bitching about making some of the older stuff easier to get because it was rewarding longevity and newer players shouldn't have access to older stuff. I want to comment and just say something like "if this is how you feel, don't ever play MTG..."
Except for the reserve list.........
A lot of the reserve list is crap, though.
With the game though if you spend enough money you'll eventually get some of that older stuff. Same w/ the reserve list.
Everyone has the same access, the bankroll is the difference

Outside of cEDH you don't see a lot of the real crazy reserve list stuff anyway. Yeah, I'm sure there are some metas where there's a huge have/have not differential where the haves are running Crypt and Cradle vs precons, but I don't think it's that common

when I build jeskai, I always want to do jeskai ascendancy

if you like glass cannons, shu yun is good

he one shots people fairly effectively though
you can make him the “you’re going down now” deck

you take him out when someone targeted you for some reason, it’s out of game politics
Vial Smasher + Kraum looks fun to me. Most Grixis commanders are niche, with a very specific strategy (nekusar wheels, marchesa counters, etc). Vial + Kraum seems flexible.

I did do a shu-yun build that was token based instead, he held up a little better for multiplayer games
and jeskai just has very little legendaries
though narset would just be better as a commander for it, just that narset has a stigma

I have a friend who put Jeleva spell-slinger together a few weeks ago. My observations; people get annoyed at the mill/exile and having their spells used against them, and they discover pretty quickly the deck is dead w out Jeleva. Both games I saw last night he didn't get much done becuase nobody let her do anything, they just either countered the cast or killed her immedietly
I see the problem
glass cannon problems!
That also might not occur in a different meta, so ymmv
Well, I didn't have my commander removed a single game last Saturday. But I was also playing Phenax :smile:

I really like under-the-radar commanders for that reason. Even when people know a deck performs well they have a hard time throwing too many resources at Reki, History of Kamigawa or Isperia, vs a Narset or Jeleva where even if the deck might be underpowered people go hard at you for the commander
Not sure if that is universal however
I think it's pretty universal and a phenomenon that's almost exclusive to EDH. The best decks dont always win becuase they are the target
